      "writtenOn": "2016-12-16T19:37:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "meta-comment\n\nMany functions have common parameters that are passed around a lot.\n\nFor one example, consider isUsingMask. It appears that this is set iff blitter is a MaskAdditiveBlitter. \nThat suggests that isUsingMask could be passed as part of blitter instead. It wouldn\u0027t need to be a virtual if that creates too much overhead.\n\nPerhaps other common parameters could also be moved to class members as well.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 638,
        "startChar": 35,
        "endLine": 638,
        "endChar": 46
      },
      "revId": "e8d1d9c81625736f6edc7f8ed9c02869420af7ee",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
