      "writtenOn": "2016-12-16T20:57:26Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you Cary for the suggestion!\n\nI did try to clean up all those arguments by creating a class called \"EdgeWalker\" that encapsulates all those arguments. However, it becomes much slower somehow (maybe because of some inline functions).\n\nOverall, the performance is quite fragile and sometimes just by re-arranging the statement could have a great impact.  Sometimes, SK_ALWAYS_INLINE can solve the problem, but sometimes I just couldn\u0027t figure out how to fix the performance regression, so I just left the current ugly code...",
      "parentUuid": "9a3953bb_4f2b01f4",
      "revId": "e8d1d9c81625736f6edc7f8ed9c02869420af7ee",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
